black.

00:51.952 --> 00:58.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think that also I wanted
to get away
from the binary, the dividing of
people.

00:58.492 --> 01:01.728 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEVE INSKEEP: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:01.762 --> 01:05.065 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:05.098 --> 01:18.445 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Tough talk on
Russia today
from the Trump nominees to run
the Pentagon

01:18.478 --> 01:20.280 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and the CIA.

01:20.314 --> 01:24.551 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At their Senate confirmation
hearings, both
men took a harder line than the
president-elect

01:24.584 --> 01:26.954 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
has on dealing with the Kremlin.

01:26.987 --> 01:31.892 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The defense secretary-designate,
retired Marine
General James Mattis, minced no
words.

01:31.925 --> 01:33.627 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

01:33.660 --> 01:34.861 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES MATTIS (RET.), Secretary
of Defense
Nominee: We have a long list of
times that

01:34.895 --> 01:38.598 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
we have tried to engage
positively with Russia.

01:38.632 --> 01:42.002 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have a relatively short list
of successes
in that regard.

01:42.035 --> 01:48.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think right now, the most
important
thing is that recognize the
reality of what

01:48.041 --> 01:53.513 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we deal with Mr. Putin and we
recognize that
he is trying to break the North
Atlantic Alliance.

01:53.547 --> 01:59.319 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: At a separate
hearing, the
CIA nominee, Kansas Congressman
Mike Pompeo,

01:59.353 --> 02:04.758 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
accused the Russians of
aggressive action
in meddling in the U.S.
presidential election.

02:04.791 --> 02:09.629 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We will take a deeper look at
today's statements
by both of these key Trump
advisers right

02:09.663 --> 02:11.431 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
after the news summary.

02:11.465 --> 02:16.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the day's other news, the
first of 3,500
U.S. troops arrived in
southwestern Poland

02:16.970 --> 02:19.840 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in a NATO buildup to deter
Russia.

02:19.873 --> 02:25.412 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Armored Brigade Combat Team
was met with
fanfare from the Polish military
and public.

02:25.445 --> 02:30.317 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. now plans to keep
troops in Poland
on an ongoing basis.

02:30.350 --> 02:33.153 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Russia charged that the U.S.
move threatens
its own security.

02:33.186 --> 02:37.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVE INSKEEP: FBI Director
James Comey will
face an investigation of his
investigation

02:37.991 --> 02:40.060 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of Hillary Clinton's e-mails.

02:40.093 --> 02:43.463 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The Justice Department's
inspector general
says he will examine what the
bureau did and

02:43.497 --> 02:45.665 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
what it said before the
election.

02:45.699 --> 02:50.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
