is a long Trump
friend who campaigned for him.

03:56.603 --> 03:59.739 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He currently heads a
cyber-security consulting
firm.

03:59.773 --> 04:04.478 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Giuliani was considered for
several Cabinet
jobs, but ultimately pulled
himself out of

04:04.511 --> 04:06.379 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the running for those.

04:06.413 --> 04:11.551 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There is also word this evening
that President
Obama will scrap a policy
allowing any Cubans

04:11.585 --> 04:14.654 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
who get to U.S. soil to stay.

04:14.688 --> 04:19.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The White House announcement
follows months
of negotiation, and it means
that Cubans trying

04:19.426 --> 04:22.362 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to flee the communist island
could be sent
back.

04:22.395 --> 04:25.432 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The existing policy had been in
effect since
1995.

04:25.465 --> 04:30.504 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVE INSKEEP: Baltimore has
committed to
changing the way its police do
business.

04:30.537 --> 04:33.273 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The city reached agreement today
with the
U.S. Justice Department.

04:33.306 --> 04:37.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They were responding to the case
of Freddie
Gray, who died after being taken
into police

04:37.878 --> 04:39.079 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
custody.

04:39.112 --> 04:40.947 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Baltimore cops will have to work
the streets
differently.

04:40.981 --> 04:43.683 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They have to change the way they
stop suspects.

04:43.717 --> 04:47.053 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And an independent monitor will
check on their
process.

04:47.087 --> 04:50.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The agreement is one of the
final acts for
Attorney General Loretta Lynch.

04:50.123 --> 04:54.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LORETTA LYNCH, U.S. Attorney
General: This
consent decree is going to
empower the community

04:54.461 --> 05:01.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and it will also strengthen the
police force
in their pure crime-fighting
role, as well

05:01.101 --> 05:03.336 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as the role that engages the
community in
that.

05:03.370 --> 05:07.507 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And with that, we hope that we
will have a
reduction in crime in Baltimore,
but more

05:07.541 --> 05:12.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
importantly an increase in the
participation
of the community in this entire
process.

05:12.879 --> 05:16.616 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVE INSKEEP: The agreement
comes after the
Justice Department found
Baltimore police

05:16.650 --> 05:20.253 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
commonly stopped poor or black
residents without
good cause.

05:20.287 --> 05:24.758 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The Environmental
Protection
Agency accused Fiat Chrysler
today of cheating

05:24.791 --> 05:26.626 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on emissions testing.

05:26.660 --> 05:32.899 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
